processinfo.head: Processing Information note
processinfo.p: Preliminary archival processing of the records was conducted by the Rockefeller Archive Center to establish intellectual and physical control of the material and assess its immediate preservation and conservation needs. The collection remains in storage boxes and original folders. Further archival processing, primarily to arrange the records to facilitate more efficient scholarly access to the collection and address its long-term preservation, will be conducted at a later date, as necessary.

relatedmaterial.head: Related Archival Materials note
relatedmaterial.p: Jackson Hole Preserve, Inc. records Laurance S. Rockefeller papers

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access note
accessrestrict.p: Records more than 15 years old are open for research with select materials restricted as noted. Brittle or damaged items are available at the discretion of RAC. Researchers interested in accessing digital media (floppy disks, CDs, DVDs, etc.) or audiovisual material (audio cassettes, VHS, etc.) in this collection must use an access surrogate. The original items may not be accessed because of preservation concerns. To request an access surrogate be made, or if you are unsure if there is an access surrogate, please contact an archivist.

bioghist.head: Biographical/Historical note
bioghist.p: Established in 1958 by Jackson Hole Preserve Inc., the American Conservation Association (ACA) was designed to carry on the educational, research, and citizen action activities that the Preserve felt was beyond its own capabilities. The ACA has supplied vital finances and leadership for initiatives to protect the park, refuge, forest, and recreation resources in this country. ACA's efforts to educate the public and secure its support have often been seminal to the establishment of important environmental and conservation organizations.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
scopecontent.p: The collection primarily consists of grant files, administrative records and financial records.

arrangement.head: Arrangement note
arrangement.p: The collection is arranged as received by Rockefeller Archive Center.

userestrict.head: Conditions Governing Use note
userestrict.p: American Conservation Association retains title, copyright and literary rights in the collection, in so far as it holds them.

American Conservation Association retains the right of prior consent with respect to any reproduction or extensive quotation of the records for publication. The Rockefeller Archive Center has authority to grant permission to cite and publish material from the collection for scholarly purposes.

acqinfo.head: Immediate Source of Acquisition note
acqinfo.p: American Conservation Association deposited the records at the Rockefeller Archive Center in April 1985.
RAC began receiving ACA records in 1990 (Accession 1990:117). Additions and accruals to the collection have been received in multiple accessions, and continue periodically as applicable.
